==English==
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm|RP}} {{IPA|en|/jɛt/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-yet.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɛt|s=1}}
===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|yet}}, {{m|enm|yit}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġīet}}, {{m|ang|gȳta}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*juta}} (compare {{cog|fy|jit}}, {{m|fy|jitte||yet}}, {{cog|nl|ooit|t=ever}}, {{cog|de|jetzt|t=now}}), compound of (1) {{m|gem-pro|*ju|pos=adv|t=ever}} (see {{m|en|aye}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂yew-}}, accusative of {{m|ine-pro|*h₂óyu|t=long time}} and (2) the {{inh|en|gem-pro|*ta|t=to,towards}} , from {{der|en|ine-pro|*do}}.<ref>Anatoly Liberman, ''An Analytic Dictionary of English Etymology: An Introduction'', s.v. “yet” (Minneapolis: U of Minnesota P, 2008), xlvi.</ref><ref>Marlies Philippa et al., eds., ''Etymologisch Woordenboek van het Nederlands'', A-Z, s.v. “ooit” (Amsterdam UP, 3 Dec. 2009): [http://www.etymologie.nl]</ref> More at {{m|en|aye}} and {{m|en|-th#Etymology 2|-th}}.
====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}
# Thus far; up to the present; up to some specified time.
## {{n-g|In negative or interrogative use, often with an expectation or potential of something happening in the future.}}
##: {{ux|en|I haven't finished '''yet'''.}}
##: {{ux|en|Have you finished '''yet'''?}}
##: {{ux|en|We do not '''yet''' know what happened.}}
##: {{ux|en|He has never '''yet''' been late for an appointment.}}
## {{n-g|In negative imperative use, asking for an action to be delayed.}}
##: ''Don't switch it on '''yet''' – wait until I've reconnected the pump.''
## {{lb|en|poetic|or|archaic}} {{n-g|In affirmative use}}: [[still]].
##: {{ux|en|He is  '''yet''' breathing. ''(He is still breathing.)''}}
##* {{RQ:Addison Christian}}
##*: facts they had heard while they were '''yet''' heathens
# At some future time; eventually.
#: {{ux|en|The riddle will be solved '''yet'''.}}
#*: {{RQ:Shakespeare Tempest|I|i|passage=He'll be hanged '''yet'''.}}
# {{lb|en|after 'have' and certain copulative verbs|followed by an infinitive}} [[not|Not]] as of the time referenced.
#: {{ux|en|I've '''yet''' to see him.'' — ''I have not yet seen him.}}
#: {{ux|en|I had '''yet''' to go to a convention.'' — ''I had not yet gone to a convention.}}
#: {{ux|en|They are '''yet''' to win a single match.'' — ''They have not yet won a single match.}}
#: {{ux|en|He seemed '''yet''' to be convinced.'' — ''He seemed not yet to have been convinced.}}
# In [[addition]].
#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=10|passage=It was a joy to snatch some brief respite, and find himself in the rectory drawing–room. Listening here was as pleasant as talking; just to watch was pleasant. The young priests who lived here wore cassocks and birettas; their faces were fine and mild, '''yet''' really strong, like the rector's face; and in their intercourse with him and his wife they seemed to be brothers.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=September 18, 2011|author=Ben Dirs|work=BBC Sport| title=[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_union/14959055.stm Rugby World Cup 2011: England 41-10 Georgia]| passage=After '''yet''' another missed penalty by Kvirikashvili from bang in front of the posts, England scored again, centre Tuilagi flying into the line and touching down under the bar.}}
#: {{ux|en|There are two hours '''yet''' to go until our destination.}}
# {{lb|en|degree}} [[even|Even]].
#: {{ux|en|K-2 is '''yet''' higher than this.}}
#: {{ux|en|Oh no! '''Yet''' more problems!}}
#* {{RQ:Bacon Sylva Sylvarum|passage=Men may not too rashly believe the confessions of witches, nor '''yet''' the evidence against them.}}
